OL,3,CMore ethnic minority graduates feel
OL,4,Cdisadvantaged in job applications
OL,6,FMore than three in five (61%) black,
OL,7,FAfrican, Caribbean or black British
OL,8,Fgraduates said this, along with 53% of
OL,9,FAsian or Asian British graduates,
OL,10,Fcompared with 51% and 49% in 2023
OL,11,Frespectively.
OL,13,FThe survey of more than 6,000 students
OL,14,Fand graduates suggests that female
OL,15,Fgraduates were more likely (15%) than
OL,16,Ftheir male peers (10%) to feel
OL,17,Fdisadvantaged because of their gender
OL,18,Fwhen applying for jobs.
